HEADWORD: Amphigen
<hw>Am"phi*gen</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'amfi`</grk> + <ets>-gen</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>amphig⟦egrave⟧ne</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An element
that in combination produces amphid salt; -- applied by Berzelius to
